  fat: 54 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1440 mg
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sheet-pan-italian-pork-meatloaves-686e22d08d751c3919190ec2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) to room temperature. Line a #baking sheet{} with #foil{} and lightly oil.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve any larger carrots lengthwise first).

> For 4 servings, use top and middle positions for roasting.

In a #large bowl{}, gently combine @ground pork{10%oz}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, ½ tsp @Italian seasoning{2/3%tbsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{3%tsp} (we used ¾ tsp; 1 1/2 tsp for 4), and @black pepper{1%tsp}. (You'll use more of the Italian Seasoning and garlic powder later.)

Form mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4) and place on one side of prepared baking sheet. (For 4, arrange meatloaves across entire sheet.)

Wash and dry bowl used for meatloaf mixture. In same bowl, combine @ketchup{1} and half the @balsamic glaze{5%tsp} (save the rest of the balsamic glaze for serving).

Brush meatloaves with half the ketchup mixture (you'll use the rest later).

Toss zucchini and carrots on empty side of baking sheet with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, ½ tsp Italian Seasoning (1 tsp for 4 servings), a big pinch of salt, and pepper. (For 4, toss zucchini and carrots on a second #baking sheet{}.)

Roast on top rack for ~{20%minutes} (you'll finish cooking the meatloaves and veggies in the next step). (For 4, roast meatloaves on middle rack and veggies on top rack.)

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, 1 tsp Italian Seasoning, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Once meatloaves have roasted ~{20%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. Carefully brush meatloaves with remaining ketchup mixture. Return to top rack until meatloaves are cooked through, glaze is tacky, and veggies are browned and tender, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

> TIP: If veggies are done before meatloaves, remove from sheet and continue roasting meatloaves.

Halve @ciabatta{1} crosswise and toast.

Spread cut sides of ciabatta with softened butter; season with remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Halve garlic bread on a diagonal.

Spread ricotta on one side of each #plate{}; pile veggies over top and drizzle with as much remaining balsamic glaze as you like. Divide meatloaves between plates and serve garlic bread on the side.